Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp
Production date: 203 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 11 Name Theuphanes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0142.01.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0748)
